1
00:00:20,541 --> 00:00:21,583
[man] Fuck.

2
00:00:23,875 --> 00:00:25,291
[sighs]

3
00:00:28,166 --> 00:00:30,250
What the hell? You caught two at once?

4
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,250
[woman] Excuse me, sir.
Would you like a lottery ticket?

5
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:38,750
I'm down on luck.
I haven't caught anything all day.

6
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,125
Sell it to someone else.

7
00:00:40,208 --> 00:00:41,291
[tense music playing]

8
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:43,791
Why don't you buy one?

9
00:00:44,666 --> 00:00:46,541
Maybe your luck will change.

10
00:00:47,041 --> 00:00:48,625
Don't you see my face?

11
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:50,166
It's unlucky.

12
00:00:51,416 --> 00:00:54,583
Ha. I think we were fated to meet.

13
00:00:55,375 --> 00:00:57,708
I happen to have a lucky amulet with me.

14
00:00:57,791 --> 00:01:00,500
It'll turn your bad luck around.

15
00:01:00,583 --> 00:01:01,750
I promise.

16
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:04,500
Keep it for yourself then.

17
00:01:05,625 --> 00:01:06,625
Are you sure?

18
00:01:07,291 --> 00:01:08,166
[exhales]

19
00:01:08,250 --> 00:01:10,250
[tense music continues]

20
00:01:10,875 --> 00:01:11,750
How about a deal?

21
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,166
You take the amulet,

22
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:16,791
and if nothing happens,
throw it in the garbage.

23
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:18,375
But if your fortune changes,

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,958
- I might have a job for you.
- What are you going on about?

25
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:25,041
[music turns mysterious]

26
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:35,291
AGENT FROM ABOVE

27
00:01:37,083 --> 00:01:41,375
A LIFETIME OF LUCK

28
00:01:46,208 --> 00:01:48,208
[eerie music playing]

29
00:02:01,541 --> 00:02:02,375
[door opens]

30
00:02:02,458 --> 00:02:03,416
[bike bell rings]

31
00:02:04,375 --> 00:02:08,541
- [laughs] Here comes the Demon King! Woo!
- No bikes allowed inside.

32
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:09,875
Hey, Hsiao-ming!

33
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:13,083
- Don't encourage him like this.
- [Hsiao-ming] He started it.

34
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:14,500
You got me in trouble.

35
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,666
Oh, he's gonna keep going?

36
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:21,000
Here comes the Demon King! Woo!

37
00:02:21,083 --> 00:02:22,125
LUCKY

38
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:27,916
- [Han Chieh] I'm off.
- Be safe.

39
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:35,666
[intriguing music playing]

40
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:06,166
[man] Hey, old man. Delivery.

41
00:03:07,208 --> 00:03:08,250
Thanks.

42
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:23,708
- [music fades]
- [gongs]

43
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:28,166
FEITI TEMPLE

44
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:37,375
- Mr. Yu, he's back.
- Hi.

45
00:03:38,458 --> 00:03:42,166
[chuckling] Hey, sir. Look!

46
00:03:44,375 --> 00:03:46,041
You won't believe it, man.

47
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:48,416
My luck was so good,
it's like I'm blessed!

48
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:53,833
The amulet brought you good luck then.

49
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,666
- [mysterious music playing]
- [chuckling] Mr. Yu.

50
00:03:57,750 --> 00:04:00,375
I'm so lucky now, what should I do?

51
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:02,791
My friend.

52
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,625
The question is, what can't you do?

53
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:08,041
Now you're a lucky guy!

54
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:10,291
[both laugh]

55
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:12,666
You're so right!

56
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,208
Okay, okay. I'll get going.

57
00:04:14,291 --> 00:04:17,000
- [chuckling] Oh.
- [chuckling] Yeah.

58
00:04:17,083 --> 00:04:19,166
[mysterious music continues]

59
00:04:21,958 --> 00:04:22,791
[chuckles]

60
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:25,625
DONGFENG MARKET

61
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:34,708
I told you to hide it well.
You've only got yourself to blame.

62
00:04:36,041 --> 00:04:37,416
It has to be Chen-Chi.

63
00:04:39,541 --> 00:04:43,000
We had the burner for a day,
and then he stole it. What does that say?

64
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,625
He's anxious.

65
00:04:47,666 --> 00:04:50,000
Well, of course. Anyway, the thief.

66
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:51,500
What's his name?

67
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,958
Su Chih-chiang, known as Silly Chang.
Got a prior for gambling and theft.

68
00:04:58,041 --> 00:05:01,666
He's stupid, all right.
Left fingerprints all over your house.

69
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:03,083
An address?

70
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:04,333
[curious music playing]

71
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:06,875
Hmm, hmm, hmm.

72
00:05:07,375 --> 00:05:10,125
- [slot machine chimes]
- [bright music playing]

73
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:15,875
According to surveillance,
Su Chih-chiang loves this place.

74
00:05:15,958 --> 00:05:17,416
So, let's see.

75
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:20,125
Whoo!

76
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:22,125
Yeah!

77
00:05:22,791 --> 00:05:24,083
Too easy, man.

78
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:30,708
I win again! It's too easy, man! [laughs]

79
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:34,291
Oh, look at this, look at this!

80
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:39,166
Oh! Look! [laughs] I think I'm gonna
win again. I dunno, man, I can feel it--

81
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:41,333
[Han] Looks like
he's on a winning streak.

82
00:05:42,083 --> 00:05:44,000
- It can't just be luck.
- Come on, man.

83
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:46,833
Unless he's cheating,
there's some trick to it.

84
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:48,500
- [laughs]
- [slot machine chimes]

85
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,708
- Yeah, baby.
- Oh. Chao's guys are outside.

86
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:54,750
All exits are covered.

87
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:56,416
Okay.

88
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,916
[Su Chih-chiang] Here it is!
It's gonna hit, man.

89
00:06:00,375 --> 00:06:02,000
- [chimes]
- [all cheer]

90
00:06:02,083 --> 00:06:05,375
- [man 1] No way! Incredible!
- [all cheering]

91
00:06:05,958 --> 00:06:07,291
- Gotcha!
- [all clamoring]

92
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:10,041
- [man 2] Get outta here.
- [action music playing]

93
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:11,208
[Han Chieh] Hey, you!

94
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,750
- Out of the way!
- [Chih-chiang] Move!

95
00:06:22,291 --> 00:06:24,291
[action music continues]

96
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,541
- Watch this.
- Stop!

97
00:06:28,708 --> 00:06:30,375
Shit. Are you okay?

98
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,458
[Su Chih-chiang] Woo-hoo!

99
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:40,000
Catch me if you can!

100
00:06:40,625 --> 00:06:41,875
[chuckles]

101
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:46,375
[man 2] You got a death wish, buddy?

102
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:56,291
- [grunts]
- [Han Chieh] Get here.

103
00:06:56,375 --> 00:07:00,125
- Where is the incense burner? Where is it?
- [groans] Let go. Let go, man.

104
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:02,041
[music fades]

105
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:03,500
[laughs] You deserve that.

106
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:05,250
[Han Chieh groans]

107
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:08,416
You all right?

108
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:13,041
Where were you? Where's Chao?

109
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:16,666
I got it wrong. We're in Section 1,
and he went to Section 2.

110
00:07:17,541 --> 00:07:19,583
[sighing] Fuck.

111
00:07:19,666 --> 00:07:21,208
We're the unlucky ones.

112
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,250
- It's Jupiter.
- It's in retrograde.

113
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:26,958
- What now?
- Let's eat something.

114
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,000
[poignant music playing]

115
00:07:57,791 --> 00:07:59,166
MESSAGE FROM WANG YU-CHING

116
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:00,583
[phone chimes]

117
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:03,583
I'M ALMOST HOME
LET'S HAVE A LATE-NIGHT SNACK

118
00:08:11,083 --> 00:08:13,083
[cell phone ringing]

119
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:17,416
Yes?

120
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,208
- [Tien-chi] <i>Mr. Wang.</i>
- [sinister music plays]

121
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:21,041
You're the guy from before.

122
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:22,958
<i>You let that thug get away with it.</i>

123
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:24,916
Hey, the police did. Not me.

124
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,750
They said he's got nothing
to do with Yu-ching at all.

125
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,375
Stupid of you to believe them.

126
00:08:32,125 --> 00:08:35,708
<i>The police were never going</i>
<i>to handle your case properly.</i>

127
00:08:35,791 --> 00:08:37,250
[sinister music continues]

128
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:41,333
[sighs] <i>Your daughter is</i>
<i>at Watergate No. 7.</i>

129
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:45,583
<i>Go now, or it will be too late.</i>

130
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:47,125
Hey.

131
00:09:03,958 --> 00:09:05,625
- You phoned police?
- [man] Yeah.

132
00:09:07,291 --> 00:09:08,375
Over there.

133
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:11,750
[sinister music continues]

134
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:18,208
[Chang Min] Thank you.

135
00:09:24,625 --> 00:09:27,208
Mr. Min, this is what we have so far.

136
00:09:29,708 --> 00:09:30,583
[Chang Min] Chao.

137
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:32,375
It's a female.

138
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:34,833
About the same age as Yu-ching.

139
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:39,250
She's headless. We'll have to wait
for the DNA report. [sighs]

140
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:41,375
- [officer 1] stop.
- [officer 2] This is a crime scene.

141
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:43,541
- Stay back.
- Sir, you can't come through.

142
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:45,916
- Oh God.
- [officer 1] Stop him! Sir.

143
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,750
- [Chang Min] Mr. Wang.
- [somber music plays]

144
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,791
- Sir, calm down!
- [Chang Min] Mr. Wang.

145
00:09:49,875 --> 00:09:52,500
- Is the body Yu-ching? Don't lie.
- [Chang Min] Easy. Calm down.

146
00:09:52,583 --> 00:09:55,041
We don't know if it's your daughter.
We have to wait for tests.

147
00:09:55,125 --> 00:09:58,000
- [Chao] Mr. Wang, please calm down.
- Is it my girl?

148
00:09:58,083 --> 00:09:59,958
- [Chao] Wait!
- [Chang Min] It may not be.

149
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:01,666
[grunts]

150
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:04,208
[somber music continues]

151
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:06,583
[Mr. Wang breathing heavily]

152
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:09,500
What is the police force for?

153
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:13,625
Why didn't you stop this happening?

154
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:18,375
Aren't you supposed to bring
criminals to justice, huh?

155
00:10:18,458 --> 00:10:20,000
Fuck you! Useless!

156
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:21,666
You're useless!

157
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:25,583
You're the ones who killed her.

158
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:29,250
You're the reason she's dead.

159
00:10:34,625 --> 00:10:36,666
[sobbing]

160
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,291
I'll kill him.

161
00:10:39,916 --> 00:10:41,250
I'll kill him.

162
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,625
Fuck, this is your fault.

163
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:46,625
This is all your fault.

164
00:10:51,166 --> 00:10:53,166
[somber music continues]

165
00:10:53,708 --> 00:10:56,291
[shouts] I'm going to kill him!

166
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:58,916
[eerie music playing]

167
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,333
[chuckling softly]

168
00:11:04,583 --> 00:11:07,458
[Mr. Yu] <i>Boss,</i>
<i>I got the sandalwood burner.</i>

169
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:09,000
<i>What should I do now?</i>

170
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:10,583
Bring it to me straight away.

171
00:11:11,083 --> 00:11:12,416
And don't tell Han.

172
00:11:12,958 --> 00:11:14,333
<i>Sure, got it.</i>

173
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:16,916
And see that…

174
00:11:18,416 --> 00:11:19,583
Han…

175
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:25,625
has plenty of jobs to keep him busy
at Dongfeng Market.

176
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:26,666
[music builds]

177
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:29,208
<i>No problem, boss. That's my specialty.</i>

178
00:11:29,291 --> 00:11:31,291
[laughs]

179
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:33,833
[music fades]

180
00:11:33,916 --> 00:11:35,916
[traffic noise]

181
00:11:42,916 --> 00:11:45,875
Hey, little cutie. We meet again.

182
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:48,708
- You here for Han?
- Yes, I am.

183
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:51,958
But he's in a very bad mood,
so I don't dare go up there.

184
00:11:52,041 --> 00:11:53,166
Don't worry about him.

185
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,583
He's always in a bad mood.

186
00:11:54,666 --> 00:11:57,083
He's actually very warm under the surface.

187
00:11:57,166 --> 00:11:58,333
[sighs]

188
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:03,125
I used to have a very psycho sugar daddy,

189
00:12:03,208 --> 00:12:05,666
who would beat me
and acted like he owned me.

190
00:12:06,666 --> 00:12:08,791
That psycho wouldn't let me leave.

191
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:11,166
It ended up being Han who saved me.

192
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:13,125
So why aren't you together?

193
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:19,375
Our situation is good.

194
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:21,041
We're both comfortable.

195
00:12:23,041 --> 00:12:24,041
[sighs]

196
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:34,000
Hmm. Is that a wig?

197
00:12:35,458 --> 00:12:36,458
Mmm.

198
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,791
I'm on chemo.

199
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,291
[poignant music playing]

200
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:52,166
In all the years I've known Han,
he's only ever fallen for one girl.

201
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:55,416
Like you, she was sick.

202
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:57,416
Huh?

203
00:12:58,583 --> 00:13:00,041
She had a disease.

204
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:03,416
You probably know
Han tried to kill himself.

205
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,083
The girl didn't have much time left.

206
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:08,875
They both wanted to give up on life.

207
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:12,708
Yet they still desperately
looked for a reason to live.

208
00:13:12,791 --> 00:13:14,875
Maybe that's how they found each other.

209
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:16,875
[poignant music continues]

210
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:19,791
Since then,
Han's never opened up to any other girl,

211
00:13:19,875 --> 00:13:22,333
and let's just say,

212
00:13:23,083 --> 00:13:25,666
I think he's not ready. [chuckles]

213
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:28,083
Works for him.

214
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,875
Look. [laughs] Look.

215
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:47,208
Wow, incredible.

216
00:13:48,166 --> 00:13:50,958
[laughing] Cheers, honey.

217
00:13:51,041 --> 00:13:55,000
Air con TV, deck chairs,
I even got them a coconut tree.

218
00:13:55,083 --> 00:13:58,625
You can't call this hell.
It's a resort. [scoffs]

219
00:14:00,083 --> 00:14:01,250
Now listen.

220
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,791
For ten years now,
you've accumulated merits,

221
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:06,458
and you don't choose
any blessings for yourself.

222
00:14:06,541 --> 00:14:07,791
Interesting.

223
00:14:07,875 --> 00:14:09,875
[poignant music continues]

224
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:14,875
[Han Chieh's mom laughing]

225
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,416
I owe them this.

226
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:20,833
Vasavatti's new agent is trouble.

227
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:23,416
Maybe I'll settle down here too.

228
00:14:24,041 --> 00:14:25,041
I doubt that.

229
00:14:25,125 --> 00:14:27,000
You'll work even harder.

230
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:31,208
You think I chose you just
because you're young and can fight?

231
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:33,416
Then why did you?

232
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:36,166
Guess.

233
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:52,333
[music fades]

234
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:53,458
Hi there.

235
00:14:55,208 --> 00:14:56,541
You're back?

236
00:14:56,625 --> 00:15:01,125
I'm having dinner with Mei-na and Ms. Lo.
Then the old man and I are playing games.

237
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:04,666
- So you're a busy girl.
- Mmm.

238
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:13,125
Are you okay?

239
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:14,291
You feeling well?

240
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,166
I'm fine.

241
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:18,541
You're the weird one.

242
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:21,791
Always such a long face,
so I keep to myself.

243
00:15:21,875 --> 00:15:23,416
I don't want to be a bother.

244
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:26,583
There are many things…

245
00:15:27,916 --> 00:15:29,500
troubling me.

246
00:15:29,583 --> 00:15:31,583
[soft music playing]

247
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:40,708
What?

248
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:42,708
You know,

249
00:15:43,458 --> 00:15:47,083
If I ever have a boyfriend,
I hope he's just like you.

250
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:49,791
[Han Chieh exhales]

251
00:15:51,541 --> 00:15:53,416
You're not only a bit thick.

252
00:15:53,916 --> 00:15:55,625
You've got bad taste.

253
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:00,625
[footsteps approaching]

254
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:05,583
Han! It's the old man. We've got trouble.

255
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:10,500
- [clamoring]
- You guys want to mess with an old man?

256
00:16:10,583 --> 00:16:12,458
You're about to get the cane.

257
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:14,125
[horns honking]

258
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,208
[laughs]

259
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:23,833
[man groaning]

260
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:26,875
[tense music playing]

261
00:16:29,375 --> 00:16:33,458
Han, these hooligans want to have
a barbecue on the roof,

262
00:16:33,541 --> 00:16:36,291
and they've requested you be their guest.

263
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:38,708
- [groaning] I, uh…
- [Mei-na] Hey, Gramps.

264
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:40,333
You okay?

265
00:16:42,958 --> 00:16:43,958
You want a barbecue?

266
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,125
Over my dead body.

267
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:47,750
[battle cries]

268
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:53,791
You're Mr. Han, correct?

269
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:56,125
Why did you offend my superiors?

270
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:57,208
Superiors?

271
00:16:57,291 --> 00:17:00,791
I rarely offend superiors.
Just lowlife like you.

272
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:01,875
Get him!

273
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:03,833
[action music playing]

274
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:08,791
[music stops]

275
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:13,541
- [funky music playing]
- [Han Chieh] Hsiao-ming!

276
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:18,250
- What is it?
- What are you doing?

277
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:20,125
Fuck, dumbass! Are you blind?

278
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:21,916
- What? That wasn't me.
- Fucking idiot…

279
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,958
The grannies said this is our turf.
They said to scare them off.

280
00:17:25,041 --> 00:17:27,083
- They'll fix things later.
- Fix it later?

281
00:17:27,166 --> 00:17:29,416
Yeah. Excuse me, will you? [screams]

282
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:31,958
[groans] Again? What the…?

283
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:36,666
- Damn you.
- What are you doing?

284
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:39,333
- [groaning]
- You're not being very good, are you?

285
00:17:39,416 --> 00:17:40,250
Oh shit.

286
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:42,083
- [funky music continues]
- Fuck.

287
00:17:42,708 --> 00:17:46,291
- Wait. What the hell? What's happening?
- [grandmas yell]

288
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:48,333
Get out of here.

289
00:17:48,416 --> 00:17:51,750
No, don't run.
Get back here. I'll kill you.

290
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:56,791
Get off.

291
00:17:58,208 --> 00:17:59,625
[Hsiao-ming] Hey! Get lost.

292
00:18:00,208 --> 00:18:01,666
Get off me. Get off me!

293
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:03,208
[groans]

294
00:18:04,791 --> 00:18:06,666
[Ms. Lo] You're still running?
Just try it.

295
00:18:06,750 --> 00:18:09,208
- [Mei-na] Where are you going?
- [Han] What do you want?

296
00:18:09,291 --> 00:18:10,833
Who sent you all here?

297
00:18:10,916 --> 00:18:11,916
Are you thick?

298
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,750
Why would I tell you anything?

299
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:15,750
This is such a mess.

300
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:17,125
- Let's go.
- [clamoring]

301
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:22,333
[Ms. Lo] Get lost!

302
00:18:22,416 --> 00:18:24,750
[action music continues]

303
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:28,125
- [man 1] That'll fix them.
- [man 2] That's right. You better run.

304
00:18:34,041 --> 00:18:36,041
[music ends]

305
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:41,208
[Ms. Lo] Haven't you two
had enough fighting?

306
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:44,208
[grandma 2] Yeah.
There's another one. One more.

307
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:45,666
- [man] Yeah.
- [Mei-na] Let me help.

308
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:47,875
[Ms. Lo] Haven't you been
beaten up enough?

309
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:50,958
- [man] Sure. I'll do it now. Looks good.
- [Ms. Lo] Hurry up.

310
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:55,458
[man 2] Over here.

311
00:18:56,041 --> 00:18:57,083
What happened?

312
00:18:57,583 --> 00:18:59,791
Some jerks turned up making trouble.

313
00:19:00,583 --> 00:19:01,625
What do you know?

314
00:19:02,291 --> 00:19:04,458
We found
an unidentified body this morning.

315
00:19:04,541 --> 00:19:06,875
The age and features are
similar to Yu-ching.

316
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:08,208
Is it her?

317
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:10,875
Don't know. We're waiting on DNA results.

318
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:12,375
But if it is Yu-ching,

319
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:15,541
then the formation's last offering
must be someone else.

320
00:19:15,625 --> 00:19:18,041
It's three days 'til the full moon,
so what now?

321
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:21,125
- [Ms. Lo] One more.
- [old man] They think they can bully us?

322
00:19:21,208 --> 00:19:22,083
Get out of here.

323
00:19:22,166 --> 00:19:26,583
In Dongfeng,
humans and ghosts work together.

324
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:28,666
- We're not that easy!
- [chuckles]

325
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,125
[eerie music playing]

326
00:19:30,208 --> 00:19:35,208
This completed formation will enable
Vasavatti to obtain his full power,

327
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:39,541
using the portal
when the moon is at its most yin.

328
00:19:39,625 --> 00:19:40,458
The portal.

329
00:19:40,541 --> 00:19:41,750
Where is it?

330
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:45,833
[Han Chieh] In the center
of the formation. Dongfeng Market.

331
00:19:45,916 --> 00:19:46,875
[grandmas moan]

332
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:49,833
- [grandma 2] Oh. This side.
- [Hsiao-ming] Other shoulder?

333
00:19:49,916 --> 00:19:53,125
[old man laughing] Next time,
they'll think twice before coming.

334
00:19:53,208 --> 00:19:54,291
[somber music plays]

335
00:19:54,375 --> 00:19:57,000
- [grandma 2] Don't forget the back.
- [grandma 1] You could do better.

336
00:19:57,083 --> 00:19:58,458
- [Hsiao-ming] Just here?
- Harder.

337
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:01,500
- [Hsiao-ming] Just here? Okay.
- Yeah. Ooh.

338
00:20:01,583 --> 00:20:03,291
- [grandma 1] You missed a spot.
- Where?

339
00:20:03,375 --> 00:20:05,375
- [grandma 1]Oh!
- Listen up.

340
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:15,041
I was going to speak
to each of you individually,

341
00:20:15,125 --> 00:20:18,250
but since you're all here,
this is probably a good time.

342
00:20:19,166 --> 00:20:21,083
[somber music continues]

343
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:27,500
A demon from hell is targeting me.

344
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:33,000
For the safety of all,
I suggest you all leave,

345
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:35,166
at least until this is over.

346
00:20:35,791 --> 00:20:39,375
I'll be staying to protect
my ghost neighbors, who can't leave.

347
00:20:41,458 --> 00:20:44,916
You want us all to go,
and leave you here by yourself?

348
00:20:45,416 --> 00:20:47,875
I will stay here. It's my duty.

349
00:20:51,875 --> 00:20:53,250
If I win,

350
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:55,833
you can return.

351
00:20:57,083 --> 00:20:58,708
But if I lose,

352
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:01,750
you should not fear.

353
00:21:02,666 --> 00:21:06,416
Another agent from above
will be appointed to handle things.

354
00:21:13,666 --> 00:21:14,916
Mr. Han.

355
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:18,291
- [grandma 1] Wait.
- [grandma 2] What do we do?

356
00:21:18,375 --> 00:21:20,583
- Are we really gonna leave?
- No way we can leave our home.

357
00:21:20,666 --> 00:21:22,958
[neighbor] I'm sure he has a reason,
but where should we go?

358
00:21:23,041 --> 00:21:24,916
[Hsiao-ming] If I don't have internet,
I'll die.

359
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,916
[grandma 2] Aren't you already dead?

360
00:21:27,708 --> 00:21:32,250
CORPSE DEMONS ARE ABOUT TO BE FORMED
FULL MOON IS APPROACHING

361
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,333
- [door opens]
- [lighter clicking]

362
00:21:35,083 --> 00:21:36,250
[door closes]

363
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:37,833
[footsteps approaching]

364
00:21:42,458 --> 00:21:44,458
[continues clicking lighter]

365
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:49,083
[Han Chieh] What?

366
00:21:54,125 --> 00:21:55,291
[Chang Min sighs]

367
00:21:55,916 --> 00:21:58,666
Everyone here will be
very sad if you lose.

368
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:01,541
[melancholy music playing]

369
00:22:01,625 --> 00:22:03,833
What about your parents?
What would they say?

370
00:22:05,333 --> 00:22:06,625
My parents?

371
00:22:08,666 --> 00:22:11,458
My parents went to hell because of me.

372
00:22:11,541 --> 00:22:13,041
I'm still atoning for my sins.

373
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:16,291
Ten years.

374
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,791
The more pain I endure, the better I feel.

375
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,166
And sleep.

376
00:22:26,750 --> 00:22:28,750
[melancholy music continues]

377
00:22:33,958 --> 00:22:35,708
My father, was he a bad man?

378
00:22:38,958 --> 00:22:39,833
I guess.

379
00:22:39,916 --> 00:22:42,375
Based on Tien-chi's verdict, he was.

380
00:22:43,625 --> 00:22:46,166
In my memories, he was good.

381
00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:48,833
Serious about work.

382
00:22:48,916 --> 00:22:50,791
Thoughtful about each case.

383
00:22:51,291 --> 00:22:53,291
Never made any mistakes.

384
00:22:54,708 --> 00:22:56,500
Judges aren't gods, I guess.

385
00:22:57,083 --> 00:23:01,250
In the end, he buckled under the pressure,
and gave Tien-chi a light sentence.

386
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:03,041
He lived with guilt.

387
00:23:03,125 --> 00:23:05,375
But then he… he took his own life.

388
00:23:05,958 --> 00:23:07,458
I guess he couldn't…

389
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:09,708
handle it.

390
00:23:12,416 --> 00:23:13,500
How much do you think

391
00:23:13,583 --> 00:23:16,875
someone who's made a mistake
must pay for his wrongdoing?

392
00:23:18,791 --> 00:23:22,833
He was a judge,
and so he sentenced himself.

393
00:23:26,250 --> 00:23:28,833
I felt bad that he was so hard on himself.

394
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:31,125
Your parents are much the same.

395
00:23:31,625 --> 00:23:33,750
They don't want you to bear this cross.

396
00:23:34,916 --> 00:23:36,916
[melancholy music continues]

397
00:23:38,583 --> 00:23:40,291
You should forgive yourself.

398
00:23:40,375 --> 00:23:43,125
You've suffered enough all these years.
Am I right?

399
00:23:59,208 --> 00:24:00,291
[music fades]

400
00:24:00,375 --> 00:24:02,375
[labored breathing]

401
00:24:02,458 --> 00:24:04,458
[suspenseful music playing]

402
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:11,708
[Tien-chi] Mr. Wang.

403
00:24:26,416 --> 00:24:28,458
You finally show your face.

404
00:24:32,416 --> 00:24:35,875
Mr. Wang, I'm so sorry
about your daughter.

405
00:24:37,541 --> 00:24:40,916
The truth is,
I really can't help you much anymore.

406
00:24:41,416 --> 00:24:43,708
I want to make sure that man pays.

407
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:46,291
I don't trust the police.

408
00:24:46,375 --> 00:24:48,750
I'm… I'm gonna put this online.

409
00:24:50,208 --> 00:24:51,041
And then what?

410
00:24:56,958 --> 00:25:01,166
All everyone takes notice of
is gossip, scandals.

411
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:06,083
Hmm. This will make the news
for a day or so.

412
00:25:07,291 --> 00:25:08,916
Maybe a week at most.

413
00:25:10,125 --> 00:25:11,208
Then what?

414
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:15,125
[sobbing] I can't accept it.

415
00:25:15,208 --> 00:25:18,916
My daughter can't die like this
without some kind of explanation--

416
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,083
I understand how you feel.

417
00:25:22,041 --> 00:25:24,041
[suspenseful music continues]

418
00:25:26,083 --> 00:25:27,666
There is another option.

419
00:25:28,416 --> 00:25:30,083
I didn't want to tell you.

420
00:25:31,625 --> 00:25:33,125
It's quite intense.

421
00:25:34,375 --> 00:25:35,958
Death is involved.

422
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:42,083
Can you do it?

423
00:25:44,625 --> 00:25:45,833
[music ends]

424
00:25:45,916 --> 00:25:48,625
TAIPEI CITY POLICE DEPARTMENT
CENTRAL DISTRICT PRECINCT

425
00:25:48,708 --> 00:25:50,333
[siren wailing]

426
00:25:56,708 --> 00:25:57,750
Have a seat.

427
00:25:59,875 --> 00:26:00,791
What's up?

428
00:26:00,875 --> 00:26:03,833
The owner's factory blew up with two dead.

429
00:26:03,916 --> 00:26:05,500
Okay. Leave you to it.

430
00:26:06,041 --> 00:26:08,041
Hey. Get in.

431
00:26:08,666 --> 00:26:10,083
You're a part of this.

432
00:26:11,458 --> 00:26:14,625
Truly, Officer,
it was an accident. What could I even do?

433
00:26:15,458 --> 00:26:18,875
What kind of accident kills two people?

434
00:26:18,958 --> 00:26:21,166
How many safety violations
are still present?

435
00:26:21,750 --> 00:26:23,541
Your factory is not even legal.

436
00:26:23,625 --> 00:26:25,708
There's illegal materials,
the workers reeked of gas--

437
00:26:25,791 --> 00:26:28,291
- [cheers] I'll be so rich!
- <i>You're in a lot of trouble.</i>

438
00:26:28,375 --> 00:26:30,250
Your best chance is to work with us.

439
00:26:31,375 --> 00:26:34,625
- When was the last inspection?
- [boss] We were never inspected.

440
00:26:37,125 --> 00:26:38,583
[tense music playing]

441
00:26:40,708 --> 00:26:42,250
You mean you bribed the inspectors?

442
00:26:42,333 --> 00:26:45,208
No! Don't slander me.
I worship God, so I was ble…

443
00:26:45,291 --> 00:26:48,083
Who do you worship, huh?
What's that around your neck?

444
00:26:51,166 --> 00:26:54,125
Mmm. This is from Feiti Temple.

445
00:26:54,208 --> 00:26:56,708
I heard that their lucky amulet
is very effective.

446
00:26:56,791 --> 00:27:00,541
I specifically went there to get one.
It's not against the law, is it?

447
00:27:01,666 --> 00:27:03,666
[tense music continues]

448
00:27:06,041 --> 00:27:08,541
This isn't a lucky amulet. It's cursed.

449
00:27:08,625 --> 00:27:11,000
It makes someone, like,
use up all the luck

450
00:27:11,083 --> 00:27:13,375
they have for
their whole life all at once.

451
00:27:13,875 --> 00:27:15,125
It's new to me.

452
00:27:15,208 --> 00:27:19,958
[sighs] Back when illegal gambling was
popular in Taiwan, they were everywhere.

453
00:27:20,458 --> 00:27:22,500
When you've got the luck,
you're untouchable.

454
00:27:22,583 --> 00:27:23,916
You're really on a roll.

455
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:26,875
When you've used it up,
you lose it all. So unlucky.

456
00:27:26,958 --> 00:27:28,625
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

457
00:27:28,708 --> 00:27:32,833
So that lady boss used up all her luck,
and that's why her factory burned down.

458
00:27:32,916 --> 00:27:34,791
How did she obtain this?

459
00:27:36,166 --> 00:27:39,166
She said she requested it
from the Feiti Temple.

460
00:27:39,250 --> 00:27:42,208
You're Mr. Han, correct?
Why did you offend my superiors?

461
00:27:42,291 --> 00:27:43,833
FEITI TEMPLE

462
00:27:45,250 --> 00:27:48,833
They came to the market
a few days ago, making trouble.

463
00:27:48,916 --> 00:27:51,458
Not long after, my apartment was robbed.

464
00:27:51,958 --> 00:27:54,416
There may be clues in the Feiti Temple.

465
00:27:54,916 --> 00:27:57,791
Yeah, but the immediate issue
is getting a search warrant.

466
00:27:57,875 --> 00:28:00,583
I can't show a lucky amulet to a judge,
can I?

467
00:28:01,666 --> 00:28:03,958
I can only charge him with burglary.

468
00:28:04,458 --> 00:28:06,208
He's lucky, all right.

469
00:28:06,291 --> 00:28:08,041
Or you'd have caught him by now.

470
00:28:11,291 --> 00:28:12,916
[snaps fingers] Hey, hey!

471
00:28:13,416 --> 00:28:15,541
You guys just give up at the first hurdle.

472
00:28:16,250 --> 00:28:20,416
If you want to fix bad luck,
you need to fix your thoughts. Got it?

473
00:28:22,083 --> 00:28:25,958
Hey, come on. I'll teach you
how to fix your bad luck. Two words.

474
00:28:28,583 --> 00:28:30,000
Inner strength.

475
00:28:30,083 --> 00:28:32,708
- Ah.
- [funky music playing]

476
00:28:32,791 --> 00:28:35,916
- [Chang Min] Oh, let's get out of here.
- Hey. Hey!

477
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:38,083
Build resilience.

478
00:28:38,166 --> 00:28:39,875
More patience will help you.

479
00:28:48,625 --> 00:28:49,750
- [sighs]
- [music stops]

480
00:28:53,250 --> 00:28:54,416
[exhales]

481
00:28:54,500 --> 00:28:56,375
[car approaching]

482
00:28:58,583 --> 00:28:59,625
The fuck?

483
00:29:01,208 --> 00:29:02,875
Young man, want a ride?

484
00:29:03,625 --> 00:29:05,708
[groans] Why am I so unlucky now?

485
00:29:07,041 --> 00:29:09,625
Be careful. Don't break my car.

486
00:29:10,500 --> 00:29:11,916
FARE: 435 NTD

487
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:13,583
FARE: 440 NTD

488
00:29:19,458 --> 00:29:23,000
Uh, uh… Sir, my wallet's missing.

489
00:29:26,333 --> 00:29:28,791
I… I'll get money out. [chuckles]

490
00:29:34,333 --> 00:29:35,583
FARE: 480 NTD

491
00:29:35,666 --> 00:29:37,375
STOP

492
00:29:40,416 --> 00:29:41,375
[door opens]

493
00:29:42,041 --> 00:29:44,375
Hey, where are we? I said I'll pay. Just…

494
00:29:44,458 --> 00:29:46,458
You should ask them.

495
00:29:48,291 --> 00:29:49,125
Uh…

496
00:29:54,250 --> 00:29:55,166
[whimpers]

497
00:29:56,625 --> 00:29:59,458
TAIPEI CITY POLICE DEPARTMENT
CENTRAL DISTRICT PRECINCT

498
00:30:00,041 --> 00:30:04,333
He said that the temple leader, Mr. Yu,
told him to steal the incense burner.

499
00:30:04,416 --> 00:30:08,625
It seems Mr. Yu is working for Tien-chi.
So that's it, right?

500
00:30:09,375 --> 00:30:12,500
We need to know
what he knows of Tien-chi's secrets.

501
00:30:12,583 --> 00:30:13,875
Give me a half hour.

502
00:30:15,458 --> 00:30:17,500
- Then you show up.
- Mm-hmm.

503
00:30:17,583 --> 00:30:19,166
FEITI TEMPLE

504
00:30:19,250 --> 00:30:20,708
[low dramatic music playing]

505
00:30:25,083 --> 00:30:27,291
- [officer] Hello, sir.
- Cuffs.

506
00:30:31,583 --> 00:30:34,375
- Ready for a fight?
- Sir? A fight?

507
00:30:35,041 --> 00:30:36,125
Who are we fighting?

508
00:30:36,625 --> 00:30:40,750
Later on, you never know, there might be
a citizen who needs our help.

509
00:30:42,208 --> 00:30:46,291
And we will come to his assistance,
and if necessary, fight bravely.

510
00:30:46,375 --> 00:30:50,291
And we will use this to protect him.

511
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:53,041
Check.

512
00:30:54,541 --> 00:30:55,708
[dramatic music builds]

513
00:30:55,791 --> 00:30:57,916
- Damn! She's hot.
- Hey.

514
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,458
Oh, shit. It's him again. Hey, stop him.

515
00:31:00,541 --> 00:31:02,291
- What do we do?
- Move. I'll get the others.

516
00:31:02,375 --> 00:31:03,458
Hey.

517
00:31:05,375 --> 00:31:07,125
[dramatic music continues]

518
00:31:08,333 --> 00:31:10,541
- Mr. Yu. I'm looking for Mr. Yu.
- [man 1] What the hell?

519
00:31:10,625 --> 00:31:12,791
What the fuck do you think you're doing?
Let him go.

520
00:31:12,875 --> 00:31:17,166
- Let him go.
- Get off him. Hey, get up. You okay?

521
00:31:17,250 --> 00:31:20,916
- What the fuck? Are you serious right now?
- What the fuck are you doing? Stop it.

522
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,458
You, bitch! Hey!

523
00:31:22,541 --> 00:31:24,750
[dramatic music continues]

524
00:31:24,833 --> 00:31:26,625
- Fuck you!
- Get off there. What the hell?

525
00:31:26,708 --> 00:31:28,916
Get down from there, right now!

526
00:31:29,416 --> 00:31:32,666
- One on one. Come on, get down, bitch!
- Get down, you fuck!

527
00:31:33,208 --> 00:31:35,041
- [man 2] Hey! Get off there.
- Feiti.

528
00:31:35,750 --> 00:31:37,875
Never heard of him. A god, is he?

529
00:31:37,958 --> 00:31:39,291
[Mr. Yu] What do you want?

530
00:31:39,875 --> 00:31:40,875
Put it down.

531
00:31:41,458 --> 00:31:43,250
- [man 1] Fuck you!
- Put it the fuck down now!

532
00:31:44,750 --> 00:31:46,083
- Fuck! Fuck you!
- Get him.

533
00:31:47,500 --> 00:31:48,875
Go get backup.

534
00:31:51,500 --> 00:31:53,250
Stay back! I'm warning you.

535
00:31:56,208 --> 00:31:58,083
[music fades]

536
00:31:58,166 --> 00:31:59,666
[Mr. Yu groaning]

537
00:32:00,250 --> 00:32:02,166
The incense burner. Where is it?

538
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:06,083
Fuck, it's in there.
I'll get it. Let me up, let me up.

539
00:32:06,166 --> 00:32:07,708
Is Yu-ching alive?

540
00:32:07,791 --> 00:32:09,041
I don't know who that is.

541
00:32:09,750 --> 00:32:11,458
- [man 2] Mr. Yu.
- Over here!

542
00:32:12,875 --> 00:32:14,500
Mr. Yu, where are you? Hey!

543
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:17,916
- [low cry]
- [dramatic music crescendos and stops]

544
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,000
Fucking idiot!

545
00:32:19,875 --> 00:32:21,000
[action music playing]

546
00:32:40,875 --> 00:32:42,125
Someone call the police?

547
00:32:43,958 --> 00:32:46,916
[Han Chieh] I did.
They hit my bat with their faces.

548
00:32:49,666 --> 00:32:52,000
- [Chang Min] Which one hit you?
- This guy here.

549
00:32:52,083 --> 00:32:54,000
He hit my foot with his stomach.

550
00:32:57,208 --> 00:32:59,708
- [officer 1] Police, don't move.
- Freeze. Hands behind your back.

551
00:32:59,791 --> 00:33:01,666
You're all under arrest! Get down!

552
00:33:01,750 --> 00:33:03,750
- Okay. Cuff 'em.
- [officer 2] Wanna make this worse?

553
00:33:03,833 --> 00:33:05,666
- You're still moving.
- [music ends]

554
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:09,083
Oh, that asshole beat me up so bad. Fuck.

555
00:33:10,541 --> 00:33:13,833
I'm the idiot if I don't escape right now.

556
00:33:20,541 --> 00:33:21,666
- Fuck.
- [siren blaring]

557
00:33:23,708 --> 00:33:24,666
[groans]

558
00:33:24,750 --> 00:33:26,833
Careful. Go easy on me.

559
00:33:26,916 --> 00:33:28,500
Cut the crap.

560
00:33:28,583 --> 00:33:31,000
You idiots can't even handle one guy.

561
00:33:32,666 --> 00:33:34,666
[footsteps approaching]

562
00:33:37,958 --> 00:33:39,625
[suspenseful music playing]

563
00:33:43,291 --> 00:33:45,291
[breathing nervously]

564
00:33:52,916 --> 00:33:53,875
Kun-hao!

565
00:33:54,458 --> 00:33:56,750
You killed my daughter, you bastard.

566
00:33:56,833 --> 00:33:58,291
So now you die.

567
00:33:58,375 --> 00:34:00,375
[breathing heavily]

568
00:34:01,333 --> 00:34:02,958
The police did nothing.

569
00:34:03,041 --> 00:34:06,666
I am the only one who will punish you!

570
00:34:14,125 --> 00:34:16,083
[suspenseful music continues]

571
00:34:23,916 --> 00:34:25,500
[knife clatters on the ground]

572
00:34:34,916 --> 00:34:37,416
[officer on radio] <i>2-3-6 reporting,</i>
<i>outer perimeter searched</i>

573
00:34:37,500 --> 00:34:38,625
<i>with no abnormalities found.</i>

574
00:34:38,708 --> 00:34:39,625
You got it?

575
00:34:40,375 --> 00:34:41,208
Yes.

576
00:34:41,708 --> 00:34:43,875
- Any leads on Yu-ching?
- [tense music plays]

577
00:34:44,541 --> 00:34:45,666
Bamboo Seven.

578
00:34:47,208 --> 00:34:49,958
<i>8-3-6 calling.</i>
<i>We've just received a report.</i>

579
00:34:50,041 --> 00:34:54,125
<i>Wang Cheng-nan stabbed a young male</i>
<i>with a knife. The suspect is at large.</i>

580
00:34:54,208 --> 00:34:57,166
<i>Location is Golden Lake Plaza.</i>
<i>I repeat, Golden Lake Plaza.</i>

581
00:34:57,250 --> 00:34:58,541
<i>Requesting assistance.</i>

582
00:34:58,625 --> 00:34:59,791
On my way.

583
00:35:01,125 --> 00:35:02,958
Oh God, Tien-chi played us.

584
00:35:03,041 --> 00:35:05,500
- Yu-ching was a distraction.
- What do you mean?

585
00:35:05,583 --> 00:35:08,208
The human sacrifice.
She's not the offering.

586
00:35:08,291 --> 00:35:12,500
Golden Lake Plaza.
It's the last location of the formation.

587
00:35:12,583 --> 00:35:14,291
Yes, it's her father.

588
00:35:14,375 --> 00:35:17,833
Tien-chi kidnapped Yu-ching
to torment her father.

589
00:35:17,916 --> 00:35:19,791
- [sobbing]
- [action music playing]

590
00:35:19,875 --> 00:35:22,666
He's consumed by revenge and hopelessness.

591
00:35:22,750 --> 00:35:25,208
Perfect offering in a human sacrifice.

592
00:35:27,833 --> 00:35:31,125
[Tien-chi] Did you know
Yu-ching's being bullied really badly?

593
00:35:31,791 --> 00:35:33,083
I'll kill him.

594
00:35:33,583 --> 00:35:35,416
I'll kill him.

595
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:36,458
Fuck.

596
00:35:36,541 --> 00:35:37,750
It's quite intense.

597
00:35:37,833 --> 00:35:39,833
Death is involved.

598
00:35:39,916 --> 00:35:42,541
But it will draw attention
to your daughter.

599
00:35:42,625 --> 00:35:45,333
- [sobbing]
- Can you do it?

600
00:35:47,708 --> 00:35:48,583
What…

601
00:35:49,875 --> 00:35:51,208
Whatever it takes.

602
00:35:52,708 --> 00:35:53,958
I beg you.

603
00:35:54,708 --> 00:35:56,291
I'll do anything.

604
00:35:57,041 --> 00:35:58,458
Do whatever it takes,

605
00:36:00,625 --> 00:36:01,708
Yu-ching.

606
00:36:03,708 --> 00:36:06,958
I killed him for you. [continues sobbing]

607
00:36:07,041 --> 00:36:09,625
I've already killed him for you.

608
00:36:14,125 --> 00:36:16,208
[music fades]

609
00:36:17,125 --> 00:36:19,125
[dramatic music builds]

610
00:36:25,625 --> 00:36:26,750
[phone vibrating]

611
00:36:31,375 --> 00:36:33,958
[Tien-chi] <i>Mr. Wang,</i>
<i>what are you waiting for?</i>

612
00:36:34,541 --> 00:36:36,125
Just one thing left to do.

613
00:36:37,208 --> 00:36:38,875
The media will eat it up.

614
00:36:38,958 --> 00:36:42,833
<i>One last step,</i>
<i>and your daughter is front page news.</i>

615
00:36:43,416 --> 00:36:45,416
[music intensifies]

616
00:36:59,833 --> 00:37:00,916
[Han Chieh] Up there.

617
00:37:02,083 --> 00:37:05,125
- Suspect's on the roof on the east side.
- Okay, let's go.

618
00:37:07,583 --> 00:37:09,208
The elevator's broken.

619
00:37:10,041 --> 00:37:12,125
What's the point in life?

620
00:37:12,666 --> 00:37:14,125
Chao, he's on the roof.

621
00:37:17,208 --> 00:37:18,750
Fuck you, Tien-chi.

622
00:37:19,250 --> 00:37:20,875
[Wang Cheng-nan sobbing]

623
00:37:23,125 --> 00:37:24,916
[dramatic music continues]

624
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,000
[faint traffic noise]

625
00:37:30,875 --> 00:37:32,875
[music intensifies]

626
00:37:43,291 --> 00:37:44,791
[sobbing]

627
00:37:50,083 --> 00:37:53,166
Yu-ching, I'm coming to see you.

628
00:37:55,625 --> 00:37:57,500
[music crescendos and stops]

629
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:04,000
[theme music playing]

630
00:39:02,458 --> 00:39:04,458
[music continues]

631
00:40:00,416 --> 00:40:02,416
[music continues]

632
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:02,291
[music continues]

633
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:05,000
[music continues]

634
00:42:57,708 --> 00:42:59,708
[music ends]
